717582f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 56th Street (West)
717582f-a.text:
Broadway, south form and including Wost 56th Street. The Broadway Taber-
nacle shown on the left, is at the N.E. corner of West 56th Street, with a
clearance (56th to 55th) just south. Across the clearance, and at the S.E.
corner of 55th Street, is the Hotel Woodward, a 12-story structure. Sil-
houetted on the skyline, is the Empire State Building.
August 24, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
